S8.title: 【ライブ】オンライン自習室 #作業用 #勉強 #自習室 study with me 2025-06-09 16:18
S8.description:
チャットで入れるオンライン作業部屋。

世界初のYoutubeライブ映像＆チャットを利用した完全自動型のオンライン入退室システム（人数無制限）（24時間）配信です。

自習室というタイトルではありますが、ここでは勉強以外のさまざまな作業（散歩，ヨガ，仮眠，瞑想，ゲーム，掃除など）もできます。

※スパム防止のため、チャンネル登録者のみモードになることがあります🙏そのときはチャンネル登録するとすぐに利用できます。

🔰【使い方】🔰
どなたでも今すぐ入室できます！
最初は次の2つのコマンドだけおぼえれば十分です。

・ルームに入って作業を始める
チャットに「!in」と書く。
作業内容もつけたい場合は「!in  作業内容」と書く。

・ルームを出る
チャットに「!out」と書く。

Botから返事があるまで待ってください。

コマンド一覧：https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/docs/essential


🍉【作業名を書くには】🍉
・入室するときに「!in   国語」のように書く。
・すでに入室している場合は、「!change   国語」のように書く。

【作業名の規制に関して】
このオンライン作業部屋では、あえて自由度の高い作業名の表現を許容しています。そのため、勉強とは関係ない作業名が目に入ることがあります。ご了承ください。


🍫【主なコマンド】🍫
・!seat
今座っている座席番号と、入室からの経過時間、自動退室までの残り時間をBotが教えてくれます。

・!席番号
席を指定して入室できます。空いている座席を画面から探してください。
（例：「!32」で32番の席に入室）

・!more
作業時間を延長する。（例：「!more  100」で100分延長）

・!break
入室中に少し休憩する。基本15分、最大30分。

・!change
作業名や入室時間の変更をする。入室時間とは、入室してから自動退室までの時間。

❓【Q&A】❓
詳細は https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/FAQ-494da77e1cd5489298500c66866f47bd

Q. 座席に座ると何が起こるのでしょう？
A. 入室するとライブ映像内に皆さんの名前や作業内容が表示されます。

Q. この自習室を使う意味って何ですか？
A. 現実の自習室や図書館に行かなくても、他の人と同じ時間・空間で勉強しているように感じることができます。また、他の人の作業内容を見て、「みんなこういうこと勉強してるんだな」「この人私と同じことやってるな」などと思えて、モチベーションがあがる人もいます。

Q. 入室時間の延長はどこまで出来ますか？
A. やろうと思えば無限にできます。例えば「!more  m=100」を100分ごとに書き続ければいいです。ただし、１つの座席に座れる時間の上限があるため、途中で強制で席移動することがあります。

Q. 自動退室って？
A. !outをし忘れることがあるので、自動退室の機能があります。自動退室までの時間は基本120分・最大360分です。入室時に指定したり、延長したりできます。

Q. 作業の累計時間はリセットできますか？
A. 累計作業時間をリセットする機能は今はありませんが、今後、週ごと・月ごとの累計作業時間をカウントする機能を追加しようと考えています。

Q. 席を書いても後にチャットした人に席が取られます
A. 遅延によってあなたにだけそう見えています😓コマンドは順番通りに処理されます。https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/d85d84bad3b24e6f8e88601f9e74df0a をご覧ください。

Q. 画面右下のタイマーの時間割ありますか？
A. https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/385f89e0e7d14be7906555e1971f9ed0

Q. これいつまで配信してますか？始まりと終わりは何時ですか？
A. 24時間365日やっています。ただ、たまにメンテナンスをしたり、配信トラブル・システムトラブルが起こって一時的に視聴できなくなることもあります。

Q. Youtubeの画面を閉じても大丈夫ですか？
A. 大丈夫です。配信を見るのをやめても退室させられることはありません。

Q. 作業せず入るだけの人が出てくると思うのですが、そこはどう考えていますか？
A. その通りで、真面目に使わない人は必ずいると思います。気にしないでください。ちなみに、累積作業時間に応じて席の色が変わるランク表示機能は、他人と比較するためではなく、自分の努力の積み重ねの指標として活用してほしいです。

Q. フードサービスは本物の食事ではないですか。本物でないなら機能の目的はなんですか
A. !orderによる注文は、あくまで仮想的なものです。このオンライン作業部屋自体が仮想的なもので、そのなかでできることを増やしています。現実ではないですが、作業のお供として活用される方もいると思います。

S16.title: 7 DAYS BACKLOLG KILLER 03/07 CHALLENGE STUDY WITH ME LIVE late night! 2025-06-09 16:18
S16.description:
*Welcome to the ultimate productivity challenge! 🚀*
For the next 7 days, we rise early morning sharp and tackle our backlogs head-on — together, live! Whether you're preparing for *JEE/NEET/CLAT/CUET/Boards* etc this is your sign to wake up early, stay consistent, and crush your goals.

*🎯 Is challenge mein milega:*
✅ Daily motivation aur consistency
✅ Pomodoro method ke saath focused study
✅ LIVE chat
✅ Discipline aur early riser mindset

*📍LIVE Timing:*
🕔 Roz subah Starting around 5 AM (flexible)
📚 Pomodoro + Break + Accountability + Fun

*❓FAQs (Frequently Asked Questions):*
*Q1. My class and stream?*
✅ I am in Class 12th (PCB) and preparing for NEET 2026.

*Q2. Can I join the challenge late?*
✅ Yes! You can join anytime. Just commit to 7 days from your start date.

*Q3. What if I miss a day?*
💡 No worries! Be honest, and restart the next day. The goal is consistency, not perfection.

*Q4. Is it only for JEE/NEET students?*
🚫 Nope! It’s for anyone with study goals!

*Q5. What should I study during the challenge?*
📝 Choose your backlog topics or weak areas and revise them during this time.

*🔍 MORE FAQs (Relatable & Personal)*
*Q6. Mujhe 5 baje uthne mein dikkat hoti hai, kya karun?*
🌅 Try sleeping early (by 10–10:30 PM), keep your phone away, and use a loud alarm (or two!). Also, watch the LIVE stream as soon as you wake up to feel part of something real.

*Q7. Study mein mann nahi lagta, kaise focus karun?*
🧠 Start with smaller targets and use the Pomodoro method. Also, seeing others study live gives you peer motivation — it's like a virtual library.

*Q8. Main abhi Class 11/12 mein hoon, kya yeh challenge mere liye sahi hai?*
✅ Bilkul! Class 11 and 12 students are the most active in this challenge. You can revise tough chapters, NCERTs, or PYQs.

*Q9. Sirf live dekhne se kuch faayda hoga kya?*
❌ Nahi. You need to actually study along, not just watch. Treat this like a real classroom – camera off, mind on!

*Q10. Agar main ek din bhi miss kar gaya toh guilt hota hai… kya karun?*
😌 Be kind to yourself. The goal is consistency over time. Bounce back next day — that’s what real discipline is.

*Q11. Mujhe lagta hai main akela hi padh raha hoon, aur sab aage nikal gaye hain.*

*Q12. Sirf 3 ghante padhai se pura backlog kaise khatam hoga?*
📅 Yeh 3 ghante base hai. Iske baad bhi aap padh sakte ho. Use this as your anchor session to start the day strong.

*Q13. Mujhe lagta hai mere doubts solve nahi ho rahe... kya aap help karte ho?*
💬 During breaks, you can ask doubts in chat. I also reply on Instagram DMs.

S40.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

Have a realistic study session with me🐐✨

Password: baphystudies 

To everyone who's studying with this:

Checklist: 
• A bottle of water, at least 1 liter. Your brain works better if it has enough water and drinking helps you to concentrate
• Your charger. You sometimes don't even notice that your device's battery is going down, so better have it plugged in all the time
• Your headphones. You will be able to focus more with headphones because it blocks background noises. Also, if it's a late night study session, you won't wake up anyone
• a tea or coffee. Coffee keeps you awake, green or black tea can make you feel more awake as well.
• Your study/work stuff:  your laptop/tablet/phone , a few pens, paper or whatever you need.
•Anything else you could need, what about a heat pad, a blanket, a good lamp, and your pet so you have a study buddy (if you have one)

Reminder: After an hour, you should stand up and walk a bit around. Better stop the music or put on different music for the break. Open your window, even if it's cold outside. Fresh air will make it better, trust me. 

You could also lay your head down on your desk for ten minutes and listen to a podcast. Or, if you have to read a book, listen to the audiobook of it. You can also listen to the audiobook while doing another thing, that's even better than listening to music while reading the book. 

I hope y'all had a good day, if not, that's okay too. Remember to take care of yourself and try to get some sleep tonight

S64.description:
Level 1: Unreliable motivation. You don't rely on it because it is outside your control. This is being lead by your emotions emotions, doing what they want, instead of what you want.

Level 2: Discipline. You can rely on this because it is within your control. You do things with no regards to your feelings about it (your motivations). The downside to discipline is that it can take you YEARS to get anywhere.

Level 3: This is where the magic happens. Reliable motivation. You can rely on it because it is under your direct control. Use your discipline to get your emotions (your motivation) to work for you, and not against you.

Practice getting into a emotional state that will pull you towards what you want. Don't feel like it? Make yourself feel like it. Direct yourself.

S83.description:
Welcome to your auditory sanctuary
In a world filled with noise, chaos, and distractions, our channel is a safe haven for your thoughts. We specialize in creating pure soundscapes—a perfect blend of white noise and gentle instrumental music designed to help you focus, relax, and find peace in your daily life. Whether you're studying, working, meditating, or just relaxing, our carefully crafted music provides the perfect background music for moments of peace and productivity.

The Science Behind Our Soundscapes
Our content is more than just great sounds—it's rooted in scientific principles that promote mental and physical well-being. Here's how our white noise and music works:

White noise helps you focus and relax

White noise contains the same energy across all frequencies, creating a "blanket of sound" that masks distracting noises like traffic, conversation, or household noises.

Research shows that white noise can improve focus by reducing auditory distractions and improving cognitive abilities.

Soothing music for balanced moods

Soft instrumental melodies, such as piano, strings, and ambient pads, stimulate the brain's reward system, releasing dopamine and reducing stress.
These melodies are combined with white noise to create a harmonious atmosphere that promotes relaxation without disrupting your focus.
Brainwave Sync

Our soundscapes are designed to promote alpha brainwaves (8-12 Hz), which are associated with a calm, focused state of mind.
Some tracks also incorporate theta brainwaves (4-7 Hz) to promote creativity and deep relaxation.
What makes us unique?
100% clean sound

No vocals, no lyrics, no distractions—just pure, uninterrupted soundscapes.
Perfect for those who need a clean, soothing listening environment.
Real field recordings

Our white noise tracks contain real-world sounds, such as rain, ocean waves, wind, and forest sounds, recorded in pristine natural environments.
These authentic recordings bring the soothing power of nature directly to your ears.
Crafted to fit every mood

Each track is carefully crafted to meet your specific needs, whether it’s to improve focus, reduce stress, aid sleep, or enhance mindfulness.
Smooth listening experience

We ensured that all tracks have no sudden volume changes or disruptive transitions, providing a smooth and consistent listening experience.
Who is this channel for?
Students and professionals
Boost your productivity with soundscapes that help you focus and stay focused.
Relaxation seekers
Escape the hustle and bustle of daily life and unwind with soothing sounds.
Sleep lovers
Fall into a deep, peaceful sleep with soothing white noise and gentle melodies.
Mindfulness practitioners
Enhance your meditation and yoga practice with sounds that promote inner peace.
Our most popular soundscape
Rainy Day Bliss

The gentle sound of raindrops combined with soft piano sounds. Perfect for studying or relaxing on a cozy afternoon.

Subscribe to our channel and join our growing community of people who value peace, focus, and relaxation. Let us accompany you to create a more focused and balanced life through the power of sound.

無論你是在趕報告、備考，還是想靜靜讀本書，這個空間裡只有書頁翻動聲與輕柔旋律。戴上耳機，讓溫暖的純音樂為你的學習時光注入平靜與動力。這不是一部普通的學習影片，而是一場「陪你讀書」的無聲陪伴，用輕快的節奏帶走壓力，用專注的氛圍點亮你的靈感✨

在綿密的雨聲與輕柔的純音樂交織中，這部影片為你打造一個獨特的沉浸式學習空間。鏡頭前的女孩專注於書頁之間，耳機隔絕外界紛擾。這不僅是一段學習實錄，更是一場心靈的陪伴——無論你是需要專注的學生、熬夜加班的職場人，還是單純渴望片刻安寧的靈魂，這部影片都能成為你書桌旁的「無聲夥伴」。
雨聲作為天然的白噪音，已被科學證實能提升大腦的專注力（參考學習心理學研究）。影片中刻意保留環境音的細膩層次——雨滴輕敲窗沿、營造出「隔絕卻不孤單」的空間感。搭配原創的輕音樂，以鋼琴與弦樂為主調，節奏緩慢而穩定，避免過度起伏干擾思緒，卻又在副歌段落加入少量木管樂器的跳躍音階，暗示「學習中偶爾的小確幸」

想象一下：深夜，窗外细雨淅沥，你坐在温暖的灯光下，戴上耳机，沉浸在学习的世界里。这份宁静与专注，正是我们为你精心打造的学习伴侣。

S84.description:
Ciao friends! I'm Kevin and here you can see me progress and join me in the deed.

I've always been uncomfortable exposing myself, yet here I am, and you might be asking yourself why in 2021 I started streaming my a-- sitting hours when I could do the same off-camera.

The honest reason is, I've been struggling with procrastination for a long time, and despite I could always achieve the expected results I wanted more and I found my solution in the Hawthorne effect, basically "if you are watched, your behavior changes in response to being observed" thus making you more productive and performant.

POOF! The procrastination curse was broken. I was - magically? - able to put in hours of focus on a certain activity without following any butterfly in the process, without any distraction from my mind.
If you want to try the Hawthorne effect on you as I did, you can tell me in chat and join me on Discord (so you can go live with me): https://discord.gg/VPnEJd6PWA.

Not only I could now focus, but I'd also gained confidence in exposing myself in the social field, meeting many wonderful people with whom we shared and keep sharing thoughts and personal events, and laugh together, and whom I can for real call friends.
A *BIG* heartfelt THANK goes to YOU ❤️, as without a viewer there would be no Hawthorne effect and no friends to chat with - there would be no progress.


How do "study with me lives" work?
There are 50/10 Pomodoro timers, where each session is made of 50 minutes of studying/working (progress time) and 10 minutes of chatting/moving (break time).

What are you working on?
I'm either studying medicine or coding.

Do you like pineapple pizza?
No.

Have you even ever tried it?
A fruit on a pizza is wrong. If you want pineapple on something get a damn fruit salad.

🧉 Hello student, how are you? It's great to have you here!
I just wanted to let you know that this study livestream is live 24 hours a day, every day of the week, so that whenever you feel like studying, you can rely on a platform that motivates you and enables you to achieve that goal. And if you ever feel like appearing on the livestream, join us on this Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]

💰💸Crowdfunding to buy a camera for the channel (since the cell phone I use as a camera is starting to give problems): https://livepix.gg/vaquinha/comprar-camera

But before we begin, if possible, please leave a like on the video, subscribe to the channel, and share your study objectives in the comments!
Finally, grab your water, matecito, coffee, or tea to stay hydrated during your study sessions.

👾 Discord link: [https://discord.gg/K5kcaMSJaU]
(To join the video call, go to the category "----- 🔴 live stream -----" and then to the channel "🔴-live-🔴")

📅 Schedule for the next livestream: [https://www.canva.com/design/DAE9uFPN...]

🍅 Pomodoro Technique:
We will be using the Pomodoro technique, which consists of four 50-minute study sessions, interspersed with 10-minute breaks. The purpose of this technique is to maintain focus for 50 minutes through conditioning. In the beginning, it might be difficult, so try starting with cycles of 15-25 minutes. However, with persistence, you can achieve the desired results!

⭐ A little bit about me and why I created this channel:
My name is Arthur, I'm 24 years old, and I'm a third-year medical student at UBA College. I created this channel to help myself maintain discipline and focus in my studies, and if possible, to also help other students do the same.
